d this game, the plains did not exist(not to any real extent)people were just begining to scale the hights of lvl 50 for the first time, and Vox and Nagafen were just beginning to feel greedy eyes upon them.<br>
 During this time, wizards abounded, they were a key element in any group, because of one simple thing. Groups got the kill from the player who did the single most amount of damage. Of course this meant wizards had the worst rep for being KSers. Lord knows i was on the wrong end of enough conflicts with them when I started. I eventually tired of it and Joined brell when it first came up, casting aside my shaman in favour of one for I was sick of being KSed. I vowed never to let it happen again, and 99% of the time, i have been successful.<br>
  Many were the wizards the followed me, they abounded, but none was more driven than I and none approached my power, and none could even consider attempting this. Then the rules changed, and aggregate of group damage replace greatest individual group damage, and the death toll of the wizard sounded. All those KSers that came to brell to become the new kings of KSing, left brell, and the numbers of this class have declined greatly. The only thing they have to offer that no other class can is access to the plains.All they can do in a group is nuke (with the rare evac) why would anyone really want a wizard in thier group unless it is in the hands of a very skilled and experienced player? The only real place they excell is in AE damage, but that is suicide to the caster, and the accepted tactics do not support it. It is just too hard to effectively use AE in a group dungeon situation.<br>
I don't really know that there is any main thrust to this post but to say that I for one am saddened by the decline of this now noble class, and respect immensely those that have the courage to see it through to thier final goal.<br>
<br>
Abrac 51st lvl wizard and Mighty Battlemage<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukalatardragyzbane.showPublicProfile>Kalatar Dragyzbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(6/16/00 3:05:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards, a endangered breed</span><hr size=1> I love a wizard in the group honestly, a talented one, a mediocre one, doesn't matter... the only trouble with wizards is mana, they have a lot, burn it quickly and they are done for a while, give a wizard a bard and an enchanter... and they can drop mobs in a hurry. You have to remember they get resisted a lot less than other casters, although you might not believe that, it's true. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/upsychodelia.showPublicProfile>Psychodelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(6/20/00 3:54:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Harvest</span><hr size=1>    All wizards now have a storebought spell just added a couple weeks ago. It is called &quot;Harvest&quot; It gives nearly a full bubble of mana every ten minutes to the wizard. It can be purchased in Neriak. It is a level 34(i think) spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
Psychodelia<br>
<br>
Evoker<br>
<br>
