-Kittenn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fazula>Fazula</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(6/25/00 2:52:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards, a endangered breed</span><hr size=1> Hmm ... I never have trouble finding a group.  People always seem to want me (even if it is merely because they think I'm cute and desire my gnomish body!).  I did over 40% of the damage on Lady Vox the other day ... no resists =)<br>
I don't think Wizards are on the decline.<br>
<br>
Fazula <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uabrac.showPublicProfile>Abrac</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(6/25/00 6:56:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards, a endangered breed</span><hr size=1> Dont get me wrong, I love the wizard class. There is something about the long 6 second sound of a wizard winding up to demolish a ha[less foe that just gets you. The fact is tho, that there are fewer and fewer wizards, both being played and new ones.I really enjoy standing up when a group is in trouble burning for a minute or two, and watching the destruction of the mobs in mere seconds.All I am saying is that it is sad to see. The wizard class has actually improved over it was when they were prolific, yet the numbers still decline. Why? The answer of course is the reduced ability to secure the kill of a contested mob.<br>
Area affect is our biggest advantage, but you need to train or practice it with another wizard and group to become proficient in it, and it is really not needed with an enchanter around, even though it is a more effecient and faster way of dealing with mobs.<br>
  Thanx for your kind words Kittenn, I really appreciate it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I also really enjoy the shaman class, they being the only class that has a bit of everything, heals buffs sow nukes dots etc WITHOUT being evil and hated everywhere.Still, it does not compare with the raw firepower of a wizard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
all hail the wizard! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukittennmeowmix.showPublicProfile>Kittenn Meowmix</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fellow of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(6/29/00 5:17:51 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/kittenn666/moghi.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards, a endangered breed</span><hr size=1> Yes Fazula is VERY SEXY thats the only reason i invited her into my FG group =) <p>-Kittenn >^..^<
Meow Meow Meow Meow</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thomus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/30/00 12:12:11 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/tomjkingt.gif width=150 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards, a endangered breed</span><hr size=1> *sighs*<br>
<br>
I love being a Wizard! - pretty much all the posts I've read hit the nail on the head. So not much else to add, other than I really think there is strength in our class if we knew how to work with an Enchanter using AE's. I personally have practiced this at great length and am convinced we need to shift focus between DD' and AE's, no Enchanter, no AE's etc.<br>
<br>
 <p><img border="0" src="http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/thomus.jpg" width="161" height="235"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/upsychodelia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psychodelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(7/31/00 12:55:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Wizards, a endangered breed</span><hr size=1>  Just wait till you get the new draught at lev 57. This ones a whopper. But seriously, I love the wizard class. Its all about taking down those first few mobs that the group pulls fast, and putting all that mana to good use. Direct damage saves your tanks the abuse, which saves your cleric's mana. BTW, many mobs lev 55+ are capable of healing/gating/summoning when low on health. A wizard will prevent this by ending their life, fast. Wizards have more mana in group situations now due to harvest and manaskin(use it!). I always like to put all the mana I have to good use. its all about timing and strategy. And when the EQ bugs mess up your pull, well thats when evac comes in handy. Oh yeah, bonds of force is a good snare too. A wizard is an excellent class, but they really need an enchnater/bard to shine, much like many other classes depend on others for effectiveness.<br>
<br>
 I certainly hope wizards arent an endangered breed. Because they can and will hurt the most powerful abominations ever to exist in Norrath. And without wizards, it wouldnt be possible. So long live the wizard!<br>
<br>
<br>
Psychodelia<br>
<br>
Evoker<br>
